    {
      "id": "7183c165-2961-4b47-b2dd-4db704574a58",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Question 4: Compare sequential search vs binary search\n\nNote that you can get the time from the system by using this function\n    long current_time = System.currentTimeMillis();\n",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "7183c165-2961-4b47-b2dd-4db704574a58"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "5b6c17b3-7c26-4fd5-81e5-765461fa594c",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "int binary_search1(int[] arr, int target){\r\n    //long cur_time = System.currentTimeMillis();\r\n    if (arr == null){ return -1;}\r\n    int left =0;\r\n    int right = arr.length -1;\r\n    while(left<=right){\r\n        int mid = left+ (-left+right)/2;\r\n        //int mid = (left+right)/2;\r\n        if(target == arr[mid]){\r\n            return mid;\r\n        }\r\n        if(target< arr[mid]){\r\n            right = mid-1;\r\n        }\r\n        if(target > arr[mid]){\r\n            left = mid +1;\r\n        }    \r\n    }\r\n    //long dur_time = System.currentTimeMillis() - cur_time;\r\n    //IO.println(dur_time);\r\n    return -1;\r\n    \r\n}\r\n\r\nint linear_search(int[] numbers, int n){\r\n    //long cur_time = System.currentTimeMillis();\r\n    int result = -1;\r\n    for (int i=0; i<numbers.length; i++){\r\n        if (numbers[i]== n){\r\n            return i;\r\n\r\n        };\r\n    };\r\n    //long dur_time = System.currentTimeMillis() - cur_time;\r\n    //IO.println(dur_time);\r\n    return -1;\r\n};\r\n\r\nint size = 10000000;\r\nint[] sorted_array = new int[size];\r\nRandom rand = new Random();\r\n\r\nfor (int i = 0; i< size; i++){\r\n    if(i == 0){\r\n        sorted_array[i] = rand.nextInt(size);\r\n    }\r\n    else{\r\n        sorted_array[i] = sorted_array[i-1] + Math.abs(rand.nextInt(100));\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nint t = sorted_array[rand.nextInt(size)];\r\n\r\n//IO.println(Arrays.toString(sorted_array));\r\nlong start_t = System.currentTimeMillis();\r\nIO.println(binary_search1(sorted_array, t));\r\nlong end_t = System.currentTimeMillis();\r\nIO.println((end_t - start_t));\r\n\r\nlong start_l = System.currentTimeMillis();\r\nIO.println(linear_search(sorted_array, t));\r\nlong end_l = System.currentTimeMillis();\r\nIO.println(end_l-start_l);\r\n// int[] arr_1;\r\n// int[] arr_2 = {1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 10, 20, 50};\r\n// IO.println(binary_search1(arr_1, 1) == -1);\r\n// IO.println(binary_search1(arr_1, 2) == -1);\r\n// IO.println(binary_search1(arr_2, 1) == 0);\r\n// IO.println(binary_search1(arr_2, 4) == 3);\r\n// IO.println(binary_search1(arr_2, 0) == -1);\r\n// IO.println(binary_search1(arr_2, 15) == -1);\r\n// IO.println(binary_search1(arr_2, 60) == -1);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "5b6c17b3-7c26-4fd5-81e5-765461fa594c",
        "executionSummary": {
